file.name: schema.yml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  title: LORIS - REST API endpoints
  description: The LORIS API uses standard HTTP error codes and the body of any response will either be empty or contain only a JSON object for any request.
  contact:
    name: LORIS Development Team
    url: 'https://github.com/aces/loris'
  license:
    name: 'GNU Public License, Version 3'
    url: 'https://opensource.org/licenses/GPL-3.0'
  version: 0.0.3
servers:
  - url: /
security:
  - ApiKeyAuth: []
paths:
  '/{candid}':
    get:
      tags:
        - Visit
      parameters:
        - name: candid
          in: path
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        '200':
          description: The module HTML page
          content:
            text/html:
              schema:
                type: string
components:
  securitySchemes:
    ApiKeyAuth:
      type: apiKey
      name: Authorization
      in: header

Error: notImplemented: path "/{candid}": get: responses: 200: contents: unsupported content types: [text/html]
